# Cursor Rules — Clinical Trial Patient Matching Agent

## Stack
- Python 3.11, FastAPI, LangGraph, ChromaDB, MLflow, Streamlit
- Pydantic v2 for API models
- pytest for testing

## Code Style
- Max line length: 100 characters
- Use type hints on all function signatures
- Docstrings on all public functions and classes
- f-strings preferred over .format()

## LangGraph Rules
- AgentState must only contain JSON-serializable types (str, int, float, bool, list, dict, None)
- Store DataFrames, numpy arrays, and model objects in _CACHE dict, not in state
- Always call _to_python() on any dict/list containing numeric values before storing in state
- Every node must handle its own exceptions and return {**state, "error": "..."} on failure

## MLflow Rules
- Always call setup_mlflow() before starting a run
- Log params for inputs, metrics for numeric outcomes, artifacts for files
- Use run_name format: f"match_{patient_id}_{timestamp}"

## Testing Rules
- Use scope="module" fixtures for expensive operations (data generation, model training)
- Use unique thread_ids in agent tests to avoid cache collisions
- Never mock the eligibility screener in integration tests — test it for real

## File Ownership
- matching_agent.py — agent orchestration only, no business logic
- eligibility_screener.py — all scoring/eligibility logic lives here
- vector_store.py — all ChromaDB interactions live here
- mlflow_tracker.py — all MLflow calls live here
